  <p>
    Two nearly identical homes can be completely different to service if one sits at the end of a long,
    soft, sloping drive and the other is a few steps from the road. In septic work, terrain and access
    aren't background details — they're often the biggest practical variables in how a job goes,
    especially across the varied ground of the Upper Cumberland. Understanding how they come into play
    helps you plan and helps a provider serve you efficiently.
  </p>

